Keyd replaces capslock with left meta (windows) key
// /etc/keyd/default.conf
	if not working, run sudo systemctl start keyd

ranger for terminal file browsing
nautilus for gui browsing
neovim for text/code editing
	\_Nvim kickstar
	\_Primeagen keybinds
Vimium extension in firefox for vim-style bindings

easygit (eg) as a git wrapper

hyprlock for lock screen
qutebrowser for vim-inspired keyboard-based browsing
pdfutils for pdfmerge and pdfmod
simple-scan to detect and interface with epson scanner (GNOME document-scanner works too)
